# Ollama Modelfile for Josiefied-Qwen3.5-0.8B-gabliterated-v1.
#
# The base model is not on the Ollama registry yet, so we pull the community
# GGUF conversion straight from Hugging Face. Ollama downloads and caches the
# blob the first time `ollama create` runs against this file.
#
# Build it with a FLAT tag (no slashes). agent-smith's OpenAI-compatible HTTP
# layer splits the request model id on "/" to recover the provider, so an
# Ollama tag containing "/" (e.g. the raw hf.co/... id) would be misrouted in
# --serve mode. Keep the tag as `josie-qwen3.5`:
#
#   ollama create josie-qwen3.5 -f configs/josie/Modelfile
#
# Swap Q4_K_M for another quant (Q8_0 is higher quality, Q3_K_M is smaller)
# from mradermacher/Josiefied-Qwen3.5-0.8B-gabliterated-v1-GGUF if you prefer.
FROM hf.co/mradermacher/Josiefied-Qwen3.5-0.8B-gabliterated-v1-GGUF:Q4_K_M

# Leave the chat template to the GGUF metadata (Qwen ChatML). We only set
# generation params and stop tokens. A 0.9B model drifts at high temperature,
# so keep it low; agent-smith overrides temperature per request via config.
PARAMETER temperature 0.3
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192
PARAMETER stop "<|im_end|>"
PARAMETER stop "<|endoftext|>"

# Default persona for direct `ollama run` testing. In agent-smith this is
# overridden by agent.system_prompt from the YAML config on every request.
SYSTEM """You are a concise, accurate senior software engineer. Prefer correct, idiomatic, well-tested code and say plainly when you are unsure."""
